race.comment: KASTUN STAR (6) won his Maiden easily at the track and then threatened at Sandown-Hillside before the near miss back here 25 days ago, heavily supported. He's been kept up to the mark with a jumpout win at Flemington and has a handy 2kg claim for this. Suited and just needs average luck from the awkward barrier. DANCING JUICE (10) resumes with a comfortable Maiden win at Kilmore and it was a tough effort following a slow start. He's still shy of his best and benefits from Cartwright's 1.5kg claim. He looks capable of taking the next step. THE MARG FACTOR (9) mixes the form but is a capable galloper suited at best. Has a 2kg claim and she can't be ruled out. BATTAGLIA (2) maps well and has been close up his last two. The 3kg claim can see him competitive.
